description:
&lt;p&gt;Due to internal staff progression Modality Partnership is looking to recruit to the role of Practice Manager at Black Country Family Practice within the Birmingham Division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be responsible for managing all operational aspects ofthe medical practiceon a day-to-day basis to ensure the effective running of the site. They will also support the Clinical Practice Director to manage a multi-disciplinary team in a way that supports the delivery of resilient, high quality patient focussed care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Practice Managerwill support and manage the staff to get the very best out of the team to enable the Practice to achieve agreed aims and objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have experience in a relevant management role with a strong understanding of NHS systems and General Practice protocols and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A recognised Level 5 management qualification or above is desirable however relevant experience in a similar role is an important requirement for the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a positive, confident and organised individual who adopts a flexible ‘can do’ attitude to your work coupled with a focus on delivery then this role within a fast-paced and continuously developing environment could be the one for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion about the role please contact Kate Jennings (HR Manager) via e-mail address kate.jennings1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date for applications is Friday 13th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
